author: mcall.com
title: College football roundup: East Stroudsburg, Kutztown
text:
Redshirt senior quarterback Matt Soltes threw for 419 yards and seven touchdowns and redshirt senior wide receiver Jon Schnaars had 11 catches for 148 yards and three TD, leading East Stroudsburg University to a 69-7 win at Cheyney in PSAC East football on Saturday afternoon at O'Shields-Stevenson Stadium.
Soltes was 27-for-39 and gained 435 total yards one week after posting 594 passing yards, 616 total yards and nine TD in a 69-67 (5OT) loss vs. Shippensburg last week. Schnaars, DII's leading receiver with 51 catches, 754 yards and 11 TD through five games, set PSAC records for catches (20) and TD (7) one week ago.
Senior wide receiver Gerard Wendowski had five catches, 118 yards and a TD for his second straight game with 100+ receiving yards after notching 10 catches, 222 yards and two TD vs. Ship.
Senior wide receiver Joe Welk had three catches for 24 yards and two TD and redshirt junior tailback Robert Healy gained 109 yards from scrimmage with 11 carries for 56 yards and four catches for 53 yards.
Redshirt senior tailback Gerald Van De Cruz had 19 carries for 96 yards and three TD, the first two from the one-yard line.
ESU gained 583 total yards, including 348 in the first half.
The Warriors' defense held Cheyney to 188 yards on 53 plays and did not allow a touchdown. Cheyney's scoring play was a 55-yard fumble return for a TD by defensive lineman Joseph Bryant early in the second quarter.
Soltes had his ninth career game with 400+ passing yards and 13th with 400+ total yards, extending both school records. He entered the week as the DII leader in passing (385.8 ypg), ranked second in total offense (415.6 ypg) and tied for second in pass TD (20).
Schnaars has 62 catches for 902 yards and 14 TD through six games. He has 37 career receiving TD, breaking a tie with Tim Strenfel (34) for second-most in school history.
West Chester 44, Kutztown 14: Kutztown battled West Chester Saturday for first place in the Pennsylvania State Athletic Conference (PSAC) Eastern Division.
West Chester (4-2, 3-0 PSAC East) controlled the line of scrimmage and took advantage of mistakes by the Golden Bears (3-3, 2-1) to build its lead. West Chester totaled 589 yards and ran nearly twice as many plays as Kutztown (80-47).
Kutztown put up 280 yards of offense, 173 through the air and 107 on the ground, and scored all of its points in the second half. Trailing 34-0, Kodi Reed hauled in a six-yard touchdown pass midway through the third quarter. It marked his school-record 26th career touchdown catch, tied for 27th in PSAC history.
Reed also added onto his school receiving yards record. He finished the day with three catches for 53 yards to improve to 2,418 career yards, 37th in PSAC history.
Kellen Williams led the team Saturday with five catches for 66 yards.
The Golden Bears blocked a punt for the second straight game. Martin Worgan blocked a punt early in the fourth quarter, and Tyler Pratt picked it up and returned it 20 yards for a touchdown.
